org.parboiled.annotations

Annotation Type SkipNode


  • @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
@Target(value=METHOD)
public @interface SkipNode
    Annotation that can be used on parser methods returning Rule objects. Instructs parboiled to not create a parse tree node for this rule. The parse tree nodes of all subrules are directly attached to the parent of this rule (or more correctly: the first ancestor not carrying @SkipNode). Note that, even though a rule carrying @SkipNode does not create a parse tree node of its own and is therefore "invisible" in the parse tree, the rule still exists as a regular rule in the rule tree and is accompanied by a "regular" rule Context during rule matching.
